Scopes:

Scopes/Variables:

1. Local Variables: 

-When function call then function goes inside the stack (stack push/insert) and then local variable introduce
-When function ends(stack pop/delete), then local variable destroy
-Local Variables has to be initialize by developer

2. Instance Variables:

-Get initialize when object is created.
-Instance variables comes in the memory when you create object.

e.g: class Emp
{
	int id; // int =0
	string name; // string = null
}

These comes in the memory when you create object.

e.g: 
Emp obj = new Emp(); // obj : reference variable

3. Static Variables:

-It comes when class is loaded in the memory, class is loaded once only.
-So static variables are bind with class, not with instance.